Apply now FAQ What does Edith cost? Instead of charging you anything up front, you‚Äôll repay your mentor 1% of your base salary for 1 year after graduation through something called an income share Read more about income share agreements What if I don‚Äôt like my mentor? Marketing professionals for small to midsize businesses wear a lot of hats content creation, email campaigns, lead generation, website maintenance, event planning, and On top of that, each month we are tasked with compiling all the data from these different areas into a report that shows ROI and trends to help leadership make decisions on future marketing It is not that we don‚Äôt have the data it‚Äôs the Reports from social media platforms, CRM systems, marketing clouds as well as Google Analytics, leave us swimming in data but pulling everything together is so difficult it feels like now we also need to be data scientists to figure out how to integrate all of Today, marketing teams also contend with the challenges of masking PII (Personally Identifiable Information). An email address combined with the demographic information compiled by online search engines must be handled with care, and encrypted before PII data must be masked or anonymized to comply with privacy laws and reduce risk of identity theft, especially if you‚Äôre sharing data with There must be a better How about building your own Data App? Since marketing professionals look so great in hats, let‚Äôs try on another ‚Äì data app Today, marketing teams, not web developers, build websites, create integrations between tools and configure the apps our team‚Äôs use on a daily However, data AI apps are still buried in the IT department and out of the reach of the business users who need the Velox is the Velox puts the focus on data, content, and use cases, not Not to worry, all the technology is there, and you can read all about it here , but I prefer to think of it as A app like everything else you use (hopefully), Velox ensures your data is highly secured and Velox is powered by machine learning and AI so over time, as you send more data to it, Velox gets smarter and can recommend, nudge, and help you make The information produced from these apps can be published to a Velox dashboard, or an API can be created to send it to your company‚Äôs preferred How does Velox work? The impact of child sexual abuse can impact a survivor in various That effects can be felt by survivors at any point in their The effects can be felt even if their abuse was reported or While survivors may struggle with any of the following effects, it is Also, hope and healing are very possible! Adult survivors of child sexual abuse generally experience mild to severe issues with one or more of the following: Guilt, shame, or blame . Sometimes we as survivors berate ourselves for not stopping the abuse, or even blame ourselves for the experience if any physical enjoyment Here, it is important to understand that a child cannot be held accountable for the feelings or decisions of an abusive Instead it is must be the person who violated that child‚Äôs right to be well and safe who should be held Intimacy with loved ones . As an adult, intimacy might be a struggle for survivors of Some survivors experience flashbacks or painful memories while engaging in sexual activity, even if it is loving and Survivors may also struggle to set boundaries that help them feel safe in relationships ‚Äì or overset those boundaries causing isolation and . Survivors may struggle with low stemming from having our personal safety violated and our right to our own bodies entirely Low can spill into almost any area of one‚Äôs life, and it‚Äôs one more reason why caring and professional help should be sought by survivors ‚Äì at any age or The important thing to remember is this: Sexual abuse is a form of trauma for which the mind‚Äôs natural reaction is to preserve and These effects, while sustaining life initially, if left for can lead to depression, isolation, addiction, violent or criminal behaviors, and even suicide as the years If you know, or even suspect that you were abused, please seek Many resources are provided under the I Need Help tab on this Hope filled tomorrows are possible for all adult and child Yes, there are personal barriers to opening up and seeking Sometimes survivors find it difficult to find a confidante and to take that first step towards But let there be no doubt that the courage required to take those steps are greatly rewarded with a more vital and abundant Is there a difference in the effects on men versus women? First, it‚Äôs important to know that the vast majority of women and men who were sexually abused will never become Instead, we as survivors tend to contend more with the issues of and overcoming social stigmas on our way toward For man and women equally, the issues of shame and are the most But in recent years, it has become clear that there is much ground to be covered in deepening our understanding of how men emotionally respond to and heal from sexual Men who seek help must first overcome the standards of masculinity that discourage men from acknowledging any experiences of Women can often come together as victims, garnering strength and personal Men would rather fight alone‚Ä¶ to their own Because of this, meeting someone who listens, believes, and respects whatever steps a man is taking toward his healing is a crucial element in a man‚Äôs If the voices of support and empathy aren‚Äôt greater than his need to avoid feelings of shame or victimhood, he will postpone his journey and may fall into increased For counselors and other professionals, men and women both seem to benefit from normalizing the fact that 1 in 6 men has experienced childhood sexual abuse and that 1 in every 5 men experience some form of sexual assault in their We as survivors of childhood sexual abuse are (tragically) more prevalent in society than most of us ever imagined ‚Äì which can help embolden men and women both and get them onto paths of Lastly, for both genders, whether a person is gay, straight or bisexual, it is well documented that sexual orientation is neither the cause nor the result of sexual Whatever the gender of their abuser that does not determine an individual‚Äôs sexual How can I know that a situation with a child is truly abusive? Physical signs of sexual abuse may be present after an incident, but the emotional and behavioral signals are much more Signs in general may include but are not limited to: Younger Children: Regression Bed wetting or loss of bowel Nightmares and night tremors Withdrawal Aggression Developmental delays Sexual behaviors that they couldn‚Äôt wouldn‚Äôt know about unless they had been sexually abused, witnessed behaviors of adults in the home or were exposed to pornography Excessive masturbation (often in public) Elementary School Age Children: Failure in school Lack of attention or concentration Lack of social skills to make or maintain friends Acting out sexually Excessive masturbation (even in class) Inappropriate sexual talk Withdrawal Aggressive behaviors toward o

What information do I send to the Servicer to present my case? The Servicer has my request proposal, what are the next steps? Are there pitfalls or hot buttons I should be aware of when dealing with the Servicer? Why not Defease and exit my CMBS Loan? What experience should an ideal Advisory Firm have? What other roles of business should my Advisory Firm have? Should I use my Attorney instead of an Advisor? Who do I contact about my distressed CMBS Loan situation? A: The initial conversation should start with the Servicer of your Loan, which is the party you send your loan payments There are three types of Servicers: Sub, Master and A Sub Servicer is typically associated with the Mortgage Company that originated your The Sub Servicer‚Äôs authority is governed by a agreement and is typically limited to document The Master Servicer‚Äôs actions are governed by the Pooling and Servicing Agreement (‚ÄúPSA‚Äù), which dictates the guidelines and authority the Master and Special Servicer The Master Servicer is the main document and collections The Master Servicer performs loan covenant tests and other administrative responsibilities, such as tax and insurance payments and managing the property Each CMBS Securitization has its own unique Pooling and Servicing Agreement, which is the document that controls the Securitization and the interaction between the The Special Servicer is also governed by the PSA to handle issues outside the Master Servicer‚Äôs purview and issues related to loan defaults, such as modifications and default Prior to implementing these actions, the Special Servicer must obtain the consent of the Designated Class Holder (DCH). The DCH typically starts as the bond buyer of the CMBS Remic Trust, but the DCH can change control as the bond incurs loan Once the loan is transferred to the Special Servicer monthly Special Servicer fees will be Complicated? An Advisory Firm with experienced professionals and contacts throughout the CMBS industry is critical and can make this process seamless and less What information do I send to the Servicer to present my case? A: If you send a two sentence proposal email you will not get your problem reviewed or resolved Providing the Servicer with a presentation that anticipates the Servicers questions and documentation needs which can be analyzed quickly and efficiently will have a much better chance of getting your request reviewed in a timely An experienced CMBS Advisor can provide a concise and complete package which can be reviewed and approved The Servicer has my request proposal, what are the next steps? A: Understanding the process of CMBS Servicing, applicable parties, and approval rights helps to set expectations and mitigate anxiety of a stressful Depending on the nature of the request, next steps may include, (but are not limited to), an appraisal, an environment assessment, various consents from the special servicer, subordinate loan holder(s), or the DCH, as well as rating agency An experienced Advisory Firm informs the client of the anticipated timeline and potential fees at the beginning of the Are there pitfalls or hot buttons I should be aware of when dealing with the Servicer? This week in Protocol Gaming, your weekly guide to the business of video games: Why this year might be all too familiar, regulators crack down on the industry and Stadia s coming to (Was this email forwarded to you? Subscribe here .) The Big Story The end of history and the last gamer As tech optimism faded in the early , Peter Thiel captured the zeitgeist with his remark , "We were promised flying cars, and instead what we got was " A similar observation could be made of the gaming industry as we enter : We were promised the next great medium for storytelling , and instead we got microtransactions and the installment of Call of Though this characterization admittedly paints with a broad brush, it s worth asking whether we re nearing the end of gaming history: Perhaps gaming isn t a medium of cultural ascendency but one of Video games once promised an escapism that would heighten our senses and enrich ordinary life, but today they act as a social palliative, better suited to numb and distract (Look no further than the slew of Reddit posts reporting bouts of depression after Cyberpunk failed to meet ) Gaming will undoubtedly progress this year in terms of technology ‚Äî Nvidia s graphics cards are as powerful and affordable as ever, Big Tech has invested heavily in cloud gaming and Facebook looks poised to push VR into the mainstream ‚Äî but that could be besides the The year ahead in gaming may instead be most remarkable in its The next generation of consoles from Sony and Microsoft are set to gain widespread adoption, helped along by the latest installments of familiar Cyberpunk s spectacularly bad rollout could mean that similarly ambitious AAA titles will have a harder time getting And though Apple is giving iOS users privacy protections that threaten mobile games, the end result will likely be more Let s take a closer Sony and Microsoft will meet demand for consoles by the summer, putting an end to console gamers buying them on the secondary market for double and triple their sticker At a Jefferies conference in November, Xbox Finance general manager Tim Stuart said that even with supply chains at full speed, he expects supply shortages will last through to the "pre-summer " An unconfirmed DigiTimes report based on industry sources claimed that Sony expects additional capacity from TSMC foundries will allow it to ship up to million units in , up from the million units shipped in the four weeks AAA exclusives arriving throughout could help Sony and Microsoft generate buzz despite the slow Innovative projects will struggle to get funding from gaming studios after the Cyberpunk Halo, God of War, Fallout, Gran Turismo, Call of Duty, Battlefield, Grand Theft Auto ‚Äî stop me if you ve heard of these releases Gaming has gone the way of Hollywood: Studio execs increasingly fund established franchises rather than ambitious projects without an established Part of this has to do with the soaring technical cost of production, which raises the stakes of failure: AAA gaming titles such as Grand Theft Auto and Destiny cost hundreds of millions of dollars to Cyberpunk was somewhat anomalous in the gaming industry given its creative ambition and AAA The title s launch struggles serve as a reminder of the risks associated with pushing the boundaries of sports simulators face a reckoning , and it could re

In , during a stint in Los Angeles putting the second original piece, Red, A New Musical, on its feet is when the confidence to start a particular niche of storytelling was The technique, the shape, the process, the sound, and feelings were to be unique to a Black lens [and including people of color]. The aspiration evolved into creating a repertoire, but done ‚Äúour way‚Äù. The World Health Organization estimates that by ( Gammon, ), NDDs will become the second leading cause of death worldwide, taking over cancer and ranking just after cardiovascular diseases (CVD). Global population growth and increased life expectancy mean that brain disorders pose an threat in developed countries, placing an unprecedented and growing strain on public healthcare The current collections of biochemical reactions that occur in the human These generic models are useful resources for computational modelling as well as network dependent However, metabolism varies in each hospitals before Disinfection vs Sterilization Disinfection and sterilization are both decontamination While disinfection reduces the level of microbial contamination , sterilization is the process of killing all pathogens , including bacterial spores, which are highly million flexible endoscopes are used in procedures in the United States During disinfection, several bacterial spores and organisms may survive, posing potential infection Disinfection does not ensure an ‚Äúoverkill‚Äô‚Äô and therefore lacks the margin of safety achieved by sterilization Moreover, after sterilization, the processed item is kept sterile either in a sealed container, pouch or bag, whereas after disinfection, the instruments are left exposed to room air and can be In particular, endoscopes are brushed and then soaked into a high level disinfectant solution which is not enough to reduce the bacterial According to the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), who published guidelines for reprocessing endoscopes in , more outbreaks have been linked to contaminated endoscopes than to any other medical Current Standards for Endoscope Reprocessing The Spaulding classification system is universally used to determine what type of disinfection or sterilization is appropriate for medical devices, and it is divided into three categories based on the risk of infection: Critical: devices that break the mucosal barrier and should be sterilized : devices that encounter mucous membranes or skin and should be sterilized or receive disinfection : devices that encounter intact skin Flexible endoscopes are considered and used in sterile body Complex endoscope design features may allow organic debris to accumulate and they should be sterilized after each procedure, however, due to their material composition, they are heat labile and cannot be steam The margin of safety associated with cleaning and disinfection of endoscopes is minimal making strict and meticulous adherence to reprocessing guidelines imperative in order to prevent between Data have demonstrated that all the steps associated with manual endoscope reprocessing are rarely performed and some essential steps are commonly This low margin of safety associated with endoscope reprocessing compares with the high margin of safety associated with cleaning and sterilization of surgical Transmission of Infection by Flexible Endoscope Disinfected flexible endoscopes have been the cause of several Carbapenem Resistant Enterobacteriaceae (CRE) outbreaks at leading major US The most challenging instruments to process in low temperature sterilization are flexible endoscopes and devices with small narrow Want to learn more? Firstly, our focus is not introducing a new financing model but rather finding innovatives ways to augment well understood existing ones and build new pathways for them on Additionally, being a saving model agnostic platform increases our scope and use A user can be part of groups that practices a well defined methodology, for example VSLA, SUSU, SACCOS in Africa, Self Help Groups, Chit Funds in South Asia, credit unions in the United States and the MiKashboks is also fully customizable to fit users‚Äô Added to that having an Open API Platform, enabling open innovation and creating immediate value to users through partnerships with fintech innovators, lending institutions, and NGOs aspiring to service millions of these groups Lastly, when we bring users online ‚Äì there is a huge opportunity to leverage tools of AI to improve their interactions with each other, experiences with service providers, and enable We build these positive pathways into how code is written keeping this vision in How does MiKashBoks handle privacy and consent issues Users govern all interactions on MiKashBoks and informed consent is part of every step of their They decide what groups they accept invitations to join and if they connect with external integrators, they initiate that connection, control permissions, and the length of that How do you safeguard data & asset security We encrypt Personally Identifiable Information (PII) and rotate encryption keys PII is accessed by our team only on user consent, example during support requests, with these audited and How do you help users find value in their data? At MiKashBoks, we regularly debate the balance between deploying summarizations and assessment algorithms, better consumed and understood but with potentially difficult to understand ethical We use artificial intelligence and data science to help make our service more convenient, impactful, and bridge that literacy gap through helping users save better, utilize credit better, and interact with MiKashboks using IVR and AI powered voice bots in their local We focus on incentivizing positive behaviour and consciously decide not to penalize unfavorable For example, positive behavior leads to pathways to discover new services from parties, while unfavorable behaviour is provided additional support like social nudges to improve, additional reminders to pay on time How are you designing for low connectivity and low literacy? language processing that aims to in the short term provide in user‚Äôs local language voice based information on theirs and their groups position and important reminders and the long terms support voice based queries and recording of We believe that this will be a game changer for truly solving for our users What is the MiKashBoks Open API Protocol The MiKashBoks Open API Protocol helps users leverage the billions of informal financial data they generate for their own economic and social The Open API Protocol enables parties to innovate on MiKashBoks along with a set of rules that govern The Legislation | Lorna Breen Heroes Foundation About About the Foundation About the Founders About Lorna The Issue The Legislation Donate Take Action In the News Select Page THE LEGISLATION The Lorna Breen Health Care Provider Protection Act The Lorna Breen Health Care Provider Protection Act , legislation that aims to reduce and prevent suicide, burnout, and mental and behavioral health conditions among health care Health care professionals have long experienced high levels of stress and burnout, and has only exacerbated the While helping their patients fight for their lives, many health care professionals are coping with their own trauma of losing patients and colleagues and fear for their own health and This bill helps promote mental and behavioral health among those working on the frontlines of the It also supports suicide and burnout prevention training in health professional training programs and increases awareness and education about suicide and mental health concerns among health care We are incredibly grateful for the of this legislation US Senators Tim Kaine (Virginia) and Jack Reed (Rhode Island), Todd Young (Indiana), and Bill Cassidy (Louisiana), US Representatives Max Rose (NY), David McKinley (WV), Anthony Brindisi (NY), Denver Riggleman (VA), Morgan Griffith (VA) and Fred Upton (MI) who originally the legislation and the dozens of legislators who have signed on to the (For a current list of , please click here for the Senate and here for the House ) We would also like to thank the growing list of industry supporters including the American Medical Association (AMA), American College of Emergency Physicians (ACEP), Association of American Medical Colleges (AAMC), the American Foundation for Suicide Prevention (AFSP) and the American Psychiatric Association (APA). The Lorna Breen Health Care Provider Protection Act ( HR ): Establishes grants for training health profession students, residents, or health care professionals in strategies to reduce and prevent suicide, burnout, mental health conditions, and substance use The grants would also help improve health care professionals‚Äô and job Seeks to identify and disseminate best practices for reducing and preventing suicide and burnout among health care professionals, training health care professionals in appropriate strategies, and promoting their mental and behavioral health and job Establishes a national education and awareness campaign targeting health care professionals to encourage them to seek support and treatment for mental and behavioral health Establishes grants for employee education, programming, and mental and behavioral health treatment health care providers in current or former hotspots will be Establishes a comprehensive study on health care professional mental and behavioral health and burnout, including the impact of the pandemic on such professionals‚Äô SENATOR TIM KAINE INTRODUCES LEGISLATION WATCH VIDEO ON FACEBOOK PRESS ANNOUNCEMENTS Kaine, Young, Reed, &
